But for how odd it seems, DJs, promoters and club owners in Berlin are adjusting to the times.
Each night at 7:00, they offer the free clubbing service "United We Stream," billing it as the world's largest virtual club.
The club scene in Berlin brings in around $1.6 billion a year for the city, and now dozens of clubs face bankruptcy.
Lutz Leichsenring, co-founder of the Berlin Club Commission, says 30% of travelers to Berlin come for the nightlife, and COVID-19 put a stop to it all.
He'll pretend he's back at his favorite crowded Berlin club with all his friends, and he will dance as if this virus never existed.